<task id="042" project="spaarke-daily-update-service-r4">
  <metadata>
    <title>Wire disabledChannels server-side $filter on sprk_category (FR-17c)</title>
    <phase>5: W2 Consumer — UX redesign + preferences + link (PR 5)</phase>
    <status>completed</status>
    <completed>2026-06-26</completed>
    <completion-notes>Added `buildDisabledChannelsFilter(disabled)` exported helper + extended `fetchNotifications` `options` with `disabledChannels?: NotificationCategory[]`. Filter syntax: OData v4 AND-of-`sprk_category ne 'cat'` per spec-line-361 fallback (no `not in` in OData v4). Single channel emits unwrapped `sprk_category ne 'cat'`; multiple wrap in parens to bind correctly when AND-joined with sibling predicates. Empty / undefined `disabledChannels` produces null clause — caller skips append (no trailing `and`). Single-quote escape (`'` → `''`) applied defensively. AND-joined with EXCLUDE_REMOVED_FILTER (always) + unreadOnly clause (conditional, task 020) + createdon timeWindow (task 040). Post-fetch dueWithinDays client filter (task 041) untouched. Tests: 10 new (4 buildDisabledChannelsFilter unit + 6 fetchNotifications behavior including AC-17c "no nested customData.category" + spec-line-361 fallback assertion). Suite: 37/37 passing. TS no errors in notificationService.ts (pre-existing workspace-package resolution errors in NarrativeBullet/SubRowTodo/useInlineTodoCreate/briefingService/dailyBriefing.registration unrelated to this task). FR-17c / AC-17c satisfied: disabled channels excluded at query layer — never reach widget OR /narrate.</completion-notes>
    <estimated-hours>1.5</estimated-hours>
    <dependencies>036, 040, 041</dependencies>
    <blocks>049</blocks>
    <tags>pcf, react, frontend</tags>
    <rigor-hint>FULL</rigor-hint>
    <rigor-reason>Code implementation modifying query layer; server-side $filter affects what reaches /narrate — visibility-impacting</rigor-reason>
    <parallel-group>E2</parallel-group>
    <parallel-safe>true</parallel-safe>
  </metadata>
  <prompt>Edit `notificationService.ts` fetchNotifications query: add `$filter` clause `sprk_category not in (&lt;disabled set&gt;)` using the existing `sprk_category` custom column on `appnotification`. Disabled channels MUST NOT reach widget OR /narrate. Pre-requisite (PR 3 task 021) is producer dual-write of `sprk_category`.</prompt>
  <role>SPAARKE platform developer. Follow ADRs strictly. Expert in Fluent UI v9 + React hooks + Xrm.WebApi.</role>
  <goal>OData `$filter` excludes disabled-channel rows at query time. Confirmed via DevTools Network tab: response payload contains zero rows with disabled `sprk_category`. /narrate is never called with disabled-category items.</goal>
  <context>
    <background>FR-17c + owner Q&amp;A 2026-06-25: Dataverse OData does NOT support `$filter` on nested JSON (`customData.category`), so producer dual-writes `sprk_category` custom column. Consumer filters server-side on that column.</background>
